DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this study is to determine whether core muscle activation is effective in the increase of quality of cardiopulmonary resuscitation.
DOC.brief_title: Effect of Core Muscles Activation for the Increase of Quality in Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation
DOC.criteria: Registered nurses who have experiences of CPR education 1. Acute/chronic pain on body 2. History of cardiovascular disease 3. History of vertebral disease including herniated disc 4. Pregnancy
